I gave this 4 forks because it is an exceptional recipe. I, too, changed the ingredients to what I had on hand (roasted zucchini, carrots, red pepper and yellow squash); warmed them in butter, added the rice, dried thyme, half of a bag of leftover baby spinach, mexican cheese blend (again, had on hand) and a can of diced sweet onion tomatoes. Wow, it was wonderful! It's the recipe that makes this....adding the cream (in my case, 1/4 cup ) gave it a scrumptiousness that otherwise might be lacking. As the reviews attest, it can be anything you want it to be! I made it last minute and will be making it again and again with whatever I have on hand!

Rating: 3
Excellent side dish for potlucks or home meals! I was looking to use some wild rice that I had slightly oversalted and I thought that a casserole might make it more palatable. I used what I had: a red onion, mixed frozen veggies (green bean, carrot, baby lima and green pea), cherry tomatoes, cheddar, and poultry seasoning instead of plain thyme. I also added a dash of garlic powder. The combination of the purple color of the onion with the brown of the wild rice and the colors of the various veggies was beautiful! It was literally photo- worthy and it was a hit at a potluck. I'll be making it again next week.

