Rating: 2
Too much fat, not enough nutritive value or flavor. I thought the corn was overkill for carbs; the rice alone does it for me, and the sweetness of the cheese and onion is sufficient contrast to the savory taste. Brown rather than white rice ups the fiber and texture if you like brown rice. I deleted the bell pepper because it imparted a bitter taste that overwhelmed the mildness of the swiss cheese, subbing chopped pre-cooked broccoli (spinach, squeezed of excess fluid, would work also) instead. I got more flavor and less fat by adding more onion, shredded parmesan (or cheddar) instead of whipping cream, and Pam instead of butter to saute the onion. Mushrooms add complexity. I also added chopped, sauteed chicken for a full-meal dish. Sorry, I guess I've totally changed the dish! Just didn't think it was worth the effort as is.

