I can't figure out why people say this dish is bland... it all depends on how much you're comfortable improvising with recipes. I added a couple of tablespoons of tamari and nutritional yeast to the rice cooker to give the rice some oomph. I used extra onion and also sauteed some garlic (bc I never leave out the garlic). I also added a box of frozen spinach together with the frozen corn and omitted the bell pepper (didn't have any). I wasn't inspired by the cheese suggestion, so I used some delicious Cotswald cheddar with flecks of thyme and a nice smooth Madrigal swiss, 50-50. I topped off the casserole with the extra cheese and then a layer of Japanese panko flakes for some much-needed crunch. It turned out great - panko is a must-have for this recipe.

