Although I was mindful of the "bland" warnings, I decided to make it as-is the first time just to see what it's supposed to be like. The only thing I skipped was the whipping cream because I don't like buying an ingredient when I know most of it will end up being thrown out. I would only advise others to do this if they're the sort of people who don't mind mac and cheese without the dab of butter. :) Bland? Definitely. I had the salt and pepper shakers out by the third bite. And yet somehow this recipe is a winner and I'm looking forward to next time and the time after that. I plan to ditch the corn for mushrooms since the corn's sweetness seems to detract from the savoury nature of the dish. I didn't have a problem with the amount of cheese on top, but then I love cheese and thought it could even use just a little more. (Keeping in mind that I used Swiss; that much Cheddar could be overbearing.) I also think Orange County's suggestion of broth is an excellent one, although I am going to try it with the other changes first before implementing that one. Also, for what it's worth, the rice I used was long-grain American Basmati ("Texmati") and my onion was a yellow (aka brown) one. Thumbs up!

